article.description: Janel McCarville had 16 points and 12 rebounds to lead No. 16 Minnesota to a 60-51 victory Wednesday night over previously unbeaten Wisconsin-Green Bay.
article.headline: Sixth straight victory for Minnesota
article.linkText: No. 16 Minnesota hands Wisc.-GB its first loss
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Janel McCarville had 16 points and 12
rebounds to lead No. 16 Minnesota to a 60-51 victory Wednesday
night over previously unbeaten Wisconsin-Green Bay.

	   It was the sixth straight victory for Minnesota (7-1), which got
12 points apiece from Jamie Broback and Shannon Schonrock, and 11
from April Calhoun.

	   Tiffany Mor led Green Bay (6-1) with a career-high 20 points,
making 9-of-13 from the field. Abby Scharlow added 11 points.

	   Calhoun and Schonrock hit the two biggest shots of the game for
the Gophers.

	   Just after Green Bay pulled within two points late in the second
half, the Gophers guards connected on back-to-back 3-pointers to
put Minnesota ahead 53-45 with just under 4 minutes left.

	   Green Bay cut the deficit to four points with 1:49 to go, but
the Gophers hit six of seven free throws in the final 33 seconds to
seal it. Minnesota was 14-of-16 (88 percent) from the free-throw
line.

	   The Phoenix shot just 2-of-13 (15 percent) from 3-point range.

	   In the first half, a backcourt steal and layup by Green Bay's
Mary Kulenkamp tied the game at 18, but Minnesota responded with an
8-0 run that included back-to-back baskets inside by McCarville,
who scored just two points in the game's first 16½ minutes.

	   Early in the second half, Green Bay battled back. Five straight
points from Kulenkamp keyed an 8-0 run that tied the score at 37
with 14 minutes left. From there it stayed a one-possession game
until the consecutive 3s by Calhoun and Schonrock.
